(126, 'INVENTORY, LOGISTICS & DISTRIBUTION MANAGEMENT', '<p>\r\n	Logistics has become a quintessential factor in modern day organisations. This course examines the core issues and skills required to promote production and distribution efficiency, reduce waste and consequently improving ROI.&nbsp; The programme will afford the personnel in Logistics to be on top of their assignments.<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	DAY ONE<br />\r\n	Inventory Management<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Introduction to basic concepts in stores keeping<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Types of Inventory (RM, WIP, FP, MRO)<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Inventory Planning and Control<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Stores Accounting and Stock-taking<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Materials Handling Techniques.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY TWO<br />\r\n	Distribution/Logistics Management<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Organisation and Management of the Warehouse, Customer service<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Distribution Planning and Transport Operations &amp; Management<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Impact of Stores/Warehousing Operations on Organisational Efficiency and Profitability<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Good Housekeeping Practices.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	DAY THREE</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Inbound Logistics<br />\r\n	Transport Operations and Management<br />\r\n	Distribution Requirement Planning<br />\r\n	Reverse Logistics<br />\r\n	Customer Service &amp; PDM.</p>\r\n', 'March 26, 2013', 'March 28, 2013', '', 'NGN100,000.00 Vat Inclusive', '2013-03-26', 547, '11', 'December 29, 2012', 1, 0, '', ''),
