(42, 'ADVANCED HUMAN RESOURCES MANAGEMENT SKILLS', '<p>\r\n	A five-day programme to raise the proficiency levels of senior HR specialists. After the programme ends, it will deepen the knowledge of the HR specialists and help with their skills in deploying human resources services to various departments, including: Employment and deployment considerations Competency development and productivity improvement Employee engagement and career advancement Remunerations and welfare statutory compliance. As line managers deserve to have a fair knowledge of how Human Resources are best managed for enterprise, the participants in this course will also learn how to encourage the line managers to complement HR services.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY ONE</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The HR Specialist&#39;s Role as a Business Partner</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Strategy Partner</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Change Agent</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Administrative Expert</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Employee Champion.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Manpower Planning &amp; Talent Management</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Objectives of a manpower plan</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Major issues in manpower planning</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Advantages of manpower planning</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; The manpower planning process</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Limiting factors</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; The changing career paradigms</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY TWO</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Recruitment</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; How the right people are attracted</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Filling vacant positions in a timely manner</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Attaining the lowest possible cost.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Deployment</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Attaching clear job descriptions to positions</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Posting employees to responsibility areas</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Movements and transfers</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Structured reporting relationships</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Grades that represent levels of authority and seniority.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Training &amp; Develop