(60, 'AGGRESSIVE MARKET PENETRATION (BATTLES FOR MARKET SHARE)', '<p>\r\n	A four-day sales and marketing training on intense and offensive market drive.&nbsp; With speed, the sales and marketing persons must:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		generate awareness for the company&rsquo;s products</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		achieve visibility in trade and outlets &ndash; wholesalers and distributors, retailers</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		maximize volume delivery and achieve company&rsquo;s objectives fast</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		grow market share for the brands.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><u>Broad Competencies Addressed</u></strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Ability to initiate more contacts and form strong relationships.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Ability to qualify prospects by performing analysis on what, when, and under what conditions they will buy.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Ability to effectively apply sales literature, promotions, tactics and offers for specific new transactions with individual prospects.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Ability to influence sales outlets by building value and encourage them to believe in the company&rsquo;s brands.</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Ability to effectively manage resistance from difficult prospects so as to make successful sales.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><u>Contents</u></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u>DAY ONE</u></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Personal Selling Skills</strong></p>\r\n<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Probing skills</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Objections handling</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		How well you know the customer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">\r\n	<li>\r\n		Sales challenges and sales differentiators</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Implementing the Sales Strategy</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Planning the Market Prospecting:\r\n		<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">\r\n			<li>\r\n				Develop the right objectives</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Identify customers&#39; real interests</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Prioritize the customers.</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Developing the Major Accounts</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Qualifying Customers - Criteria for Prioritizing\r\n		<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">\r\n			<li>\r\n				Potential size of account</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				History of patronage</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Previous relationship on other platforms</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Pressing need for product/service</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Clear cost-benefit relationship - positive attitude</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Financial soundness of the customer</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				Customer accessibility.</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u>DAY TWO</u></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Outlets Management</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Territory Management\r\n		<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">\r\n			<li>\r\n				territory delineation</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				route planning</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				the Selling Process &ndash; Call Plans</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				sales target for the period</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				merchandising</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				other objectives for the period</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				adding new prospects and deleting &ldquo;dogs&rdquo;.</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Relationship Management Competencies</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Offer Analysis\r\n		<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">\r\n			<li>\r\n				Customer benefits</li>\r\n			<li>\r\n				What&rsquo;s special about you &ndash; the Appeal</li>\r\n		</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="margin-left: 2.5in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<u>DAY THREE</u></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Profitable Negotiation</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Rules of commercial negotiation\r\n		<ul style="list-style-type: circle;">\r\n			<li>\r\n				No negotiation when selling is unsure</li>\r\n			