(73, 'A MANAGER''S PERSONAL EFFECTIVENESS', '<p>\r\n	This course is about what managers can do specifically to improve their individual effectiveness and enhance productivity for the organization. The programme contents have been developed around seven &quot;Key Questions&quot; which managers must continually answer for themselves. The questions are: What have I been hired to do? What results are expected of me? What can I do to make a real difference in the organization?s fortunes? What are my bosses? Critical Result Areas? What Critical Result Areas should be for my subordinates? What do I value most in my life? What do I want to achieve my goals: Long term? Short term? Professionally? Socially?</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY ONE</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Planning Orientation</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; The discipline of planning and preparation to avoid unplanned catastrophes:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	o short term planning: daily/weekly/monthly</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	o long term planning: self development outlook.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Recognise and take full advantage of limited resources.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Focus awareness on company procedures.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Time discipline.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Business Knowledge</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Strong knowledge of the organization&rsquo;s business.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Appreciation of their decisions and actions which touch the business bottom line.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Application of competence to see jobs delivered cost effectively.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Performance Orientation</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Focus on delivering results - work efficiently and creatively to meet agreed goals and objectives.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Define personal responsibilities.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Be clear about standards.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Review self performance against set goals.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Opportunities Focused</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Understand what opportunities exist or can be created, and convert them into results.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Take advantage of opportunities for success in the present or future.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Create new ways of doing things that are beneficial, advantageous or profitable.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Problem Solving</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Identify forms of waste to reduce losses.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Make adjustments to accommodate changing situations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Respond resourcefully to new demands or circumstances.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY TWO</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Innovativeness</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Experiment and be adventurous.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Develop new thinking and skills and challenge yourself.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Initiative</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Anticipate business needs to proactively create solutions.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Take on difficult tasks in order to achieve business results.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Delegation and Empowerment</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Willingly delegate.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Provide subordinates with opportunities to prove their capabilities.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Assign the appropriate degree of authority.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Provide assistance and support.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Champion Relevant Changes</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Strive for learning and growth.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Structure process for quality and efficiency.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Developing Self</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Strive for learning and growth both professionally and personally.</p>\r\n', 'April 25, 2013', 'April 26, 2013', '', 'NGN80,000.00 Vat Inclusive', '2013-04-25', 522, '9', '', 1, 0, '', ''),
