(149, 'GUIDES TO SETTING UP A NEW HR DEPARTMENT', '<p>\r\n	This course provides the information HR officers need to establish a human resource function in new, small and medium size companies or companies opening an HR department for the first time. It treats matters relating to HR policies, guidelines, procedures, records and information.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Contents</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Day One</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Roles of the HR Professional</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Operational and Strategic</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Partnering and Policing</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Qualitative and Quantitative</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Short term and Long term.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Recruiting, Selection and Deployment Processes</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Personnel requirements and requisition</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Recruitment procedures</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Orientation/Onboarding of new employees</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Employee deployment.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Day Two</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Personnel Recordkeeping</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Information to include in employee file</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Regulatory compliance</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Payroll</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Record retention requirements.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Personnel Policies</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Policy Manual</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Staff Handbook</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Personnel communication channels.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Day Three</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Compensation and Benefits</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Researching industry practice</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Designing a compensation programme</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Job evaluation</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Wage grades</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Payroll management</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Pay-for-Performance</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Tax, pension and other statutory compliance.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Performance Management</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Jo