(80, 'EXCELLENT REPORT AND PROPOSAL WRITING SKILLS', '<p>\r\n	Programme Description<br />\r\n	For effectiveness in business communications, this course focuses on making managers to:<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Become highly skilled in the use of English language.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Write memos, letters, reports, proposals excellently by presenting their contents with mechanical precision.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Organise their thoughts clearly before writing.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Know the techniques of outlining, drafting and revising their written messages.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Practice writing styles that are clear, concrete and courteous.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Pay attention to their spellings and punctuations.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Know the rules that guide the use numerals in their written messages.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	DAY ONE<br />\r\n	The Challenge of Communicating Effectively<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;The business case<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Communication and culture.<br />\r\n	Writing Guidelines<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Essence of effective business writing<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Planning the writing<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Organizing thought before writing.<br />\r\n	Prewriting &amp; Planning<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Establishing purpose<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Clarifying readership<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Researching for facts.<br />\r\n	Doing the Writing<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Word usage<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Common errors in our use of English by Nigerians<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Word economy.<br />\r\n	&nbsp;<br />\r\n	The Business Writer&rsquo;s Attitudes<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Simplicity and conciseness<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Confused words<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Outdated expressions<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Opinion words and expressions<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Look-alike words.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY TWO<br />\r\n	Attention to Grammar<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Verb exercises<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Noun and pronoun exercises<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Spellings<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Punctu