(87, 'SKILLFUL BUSINESS NEGOTIATION (THE PRINCIPLES AND THE PRACTICE)', '<p>\r\n	A training programme whose contents have been developed around six &ldquo;Key Negotiation Lessons&rdquo;, namely:<br />\r\n	1.&nbsp;Avoid unreasonable or arbitrary positions<br />\r\n	2.&nbsp;Avoid letting prejudices show through<br />\r\n	3.&nbsp;Avoid negotiating by demands and ultimatums<br />\r\n	4.&nbsp;Present arguments calmly, without personalizing<br />\r\n	5.&nbsp;Explain positions logically and frankly<br />\r\n	6.&nbsp;Recognize legitimate concerns and needs of other side.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Broad Competencies Addressed<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Ability to assess one&rsquo;s central negotiating style &ndash; collaborate, compromise, defeat, withdraw or accommodate.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Ability to assess one&rsquo;s true power in any negotiation process.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Ability to concede without losing out.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Ability to employ any of the several tactics negotiators use and manage when any of the tactics are being tried by other parties.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Ability to assess a true crisis situation and not a contrived one, so as to employ the right crisis negotiating tactics at the right time.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	DAY ONE<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Three Rules For Commercial Negotiations<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Cost of Negotiated Solution<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Negotiating Concerns<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Interests, needs and alternatives in a negotiation<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;How to Improve Your Negotiating Results</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY TWO<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Basic Negotiation Styles<br />\r\n	o&nbsp;Win-lose<br />\r\n	o&nbsp;Lose- lose<br />\r\n	o&nbsp;Compromise<br />\r\n	o&nbsp;Collaborate<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;The Essential Preparations<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Timing for Negotiation Advantage<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;The Five Types Of Power in a Negotiation Process<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Managing Your Ego<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Closing with Confirmation</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY THREE<br />\r\n	Negotiating Positions:<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Terms and Conditions<br />\r\n	Negotiating Interests:<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Underlying motivations<br />\r\n	Negotiating Options:<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Inventing an option is not a commitment<br />\r\n	Negotiating Standards:<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Make the negotiation a joint search for independent standards<br />\r\n	People Issues:<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Ease and tone of communication<br />\r\n	Negotiation Alternatives (BATNA)<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;The only authentic strength a negotiator possesses<br />\r\n	Negotiation Tactics:<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Glossary of Tactics<br />\r\n	Negotiation Planner:<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;A practice with the Negotiation Planner.</p>\r\n', 'February 6, 2013', 'February 8, 2013', '', 'NGN100,000.00 Vat Inclusive', '2013-02-06', 452, '9', '', 1, 0, '', ''),
(88, 'SKILLFUL BUSINESS NEGOTIATION (THE PRINCIPLES AND THE PRACTICE)', '<p>\r\n	A training programme whose contents have been developed around six &ldquo;Key Negotiation Lessons&rdquo;, namely:<br />\r\n	1.&nbsp;Avoid unreasonable or arbitrary positions<br />\r\n	2.&nbsp;Avoid letting prejudices show through<br />\r\n	3.&nbsp;Avoid negotiating by demands and ultimatums<br />\r\n	4.&nbsp;Present arguments calmly, without personalizing<br />\r\n	5.&nbsp;Explain positions logically and frankly<br />\r\n	6.&nbsp;Recognize legitimate concerns and needs of other side.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Broad Competencies Addressed<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Ability to assess one&rsquo;s central negotiating style &ndash; collaborate, compromise, defeat, withdraw or accommodate.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Ability to assess one&rsquo;s true power in any negotiation process.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Ability to concede without losing out.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Ability to employ any of the several tactics negotiators use and manage when any of the tactics are being tried by other parties.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Ability to assess a true crisis situation and not a contrived one, so as to employ the right crisis negotiating tactics at the right time.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	DAY ONE<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Three Rules For Commercial Negotiations<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Cost of Negotiated Solution<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Negotiating Concerns<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Interests, needs and alternatives in a negotiation<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;How to Improve Your Negotiating Results</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY TWO<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Basic Negotiation Styles<br />\r\n	o&nbsp;Win-lose<br />\r\n	o&nbsp;Lose- lose<br />\r\n	o&nbsp;Compromise<br />\r\n	o&nbsp;Collaborate<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;The Essential Preparations<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Timing for Negotiation Advantage<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;The Five Types Of Power in a Negotiation Process<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Managing Your Ego<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Closing with Confirmation</p>\r\n<p