(107, 'HOW TO FIND AND WIN NEW BUSINESS', '<p>\r\n	Focus of the Course:&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;How to plan prospecting for new customers.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;How to position the company and product appropriately to attract the right prospects&#39; desires and patronage.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;How to do the prospecting itself.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;How to develop useful leads.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;How to develop relationship management capabilities.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<br />\r\n	DAY ONE<br />\r\n	Types of Prospects<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Successful Prospect<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Prospect with Problem<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Complacent or Satisfied Prospect<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Negative or Difficult Prospect</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Attributes of Excellent Prospects</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Planning the Prospecting for New Business<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Develop the right objectives.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Identify prospects&#39; real interests.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Prioritize the prospects.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Develop marketing plan.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Leads<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Sources of Prospects<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Generate useful leads<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Find and nurture key contacts.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Managing the new relationship effectively.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY TWO<br />\r\n	Positioning<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Sell your value.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Be first or create a new category with the prospect.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;The R3 winner&#39;s formula.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Prospecting<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Analyzing your product<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Analyzing your market<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Develop the right objectives.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;The conventional tricks: mails, referrals, etc.<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;More business from known clients.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Prospecting Strategy<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Who exactly is my probable customer?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Where is my prospect?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Why may my probable customer buy - Buying Influences?<br />\r\n	&bull;&n