(110, 'MANAGING DISTRIBUTION CHANNELS EFFECTIVELY', '<p>\r\n	Channels must be managed in a coherent manner if the business will achieve increased profitability. This programme will address the skill improvement and tool sharpening requirements of sales and marketing managers to improve overall management of distribution.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAYONE</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Issues to consider in a channel of distribution</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Issues that are critical to effective channel coordination</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Optimising dealership and retail structures to meet the end users&rsquo; demands.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Issues that affect intensity of distribution</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Allocating resources to Channel Members</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Assessing Demand Side/Supply Side Gaps in the current strategy</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Analysing the channel gaps</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Distinguishing the Demand Side and Supply Side gaps</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Effective tools to address the gaps.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY TWO</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Wholesale and retail coordination</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Designing healthy competitive programmes for the Wholesalers and Retailers</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Harmonizing the goals of the different Channel Members</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Providing adequate knowledge to and motivating Wholesalers and Retailers</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Channel conflicts</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Types of channels conflict</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Tools for effective channel conflict management</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Influencing channel members behaviour</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Antecedents behaviour and rewards system</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Sources of power and its usage by dealers</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Doing more with less through partnering.</p>\r\n', 'February 27, 2013', 'February 28, 2013', '', 'NGN80,000.00 Vat Inclusive', '2013-02-27', 676, '7', '', 1, 0, '', ''),
(111, 'MANAGING DISTRIBUTION CHANNELS EFFECTIVELY', '<p>\r\n	Channels must be managed in a coherent manner if the business will achieve increased profitability. This programme will address the skill improvement and tool sharpening requirements of sales and marketing managers to improve overall management of distribution.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAYONE</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Issues to consider in a channel of distribution</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Issues that are critical to effective channel coordination</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Optimising dealership and retail structures to meet the end users&rsquo; demands.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Issues that affect intensity of distribution</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Allocating resources to Channel Members</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Assessing Demand Side/Supply Side Gaps in the current strategy</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Analysing the channel gaps</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Distinguishing the Demand Side and Supply Side gaps</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Effective tools to address the gaps.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY TWO</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Wholesale and retail coordination</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Designing healthy competitive programmes for the Wholesalers and Retailers</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Harmonizing the goals of the different Channel Members</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Providing adequate knowledge to and motivating Wholesalers and Retailers</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Channel conflicts</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Types of channels conflict</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Tools for effective channel conflict management</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Influencing channel members behaviour</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Antecedents behaviour and rewards system</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Sources of power and its usage by dealers</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&bull; Doing more with less through partnering.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'July 25, 2013', 'July 26, 2013', '', 'NGN80,000.00 Vat Inclusive', '2013-07-25', 479, '7', '', 1, 0, '', ''),
(131, 'PETROLEUM PRODUCTS RETAIL MARKETING ( THE FOUNDATION COURSE )', '<p>\r\n	This course focuses on the fundamental knowledge and skills needed to maximize returns from outlets and on networks and branding. It is a broad based, comprehensive foundation course for managing objectives and resources professionally in this line of business. Retail marketing in today&rsquo;s oil industry is not only about fuels and lubes. Ever more discerning customers need a wider range of goods and services. Increasing competition is putting margins under pressure. The course explores the circumstances and problems affecting the retail oil industry and it considers the solutions available to wholesalers and retailers. It deals with fundamentals affecting supply, marketing and retailing of fuels and associated goods and services, and how technology can help secure success in the market place.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	What participants will learn<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;How to optimise retail networks, brands, property and on-site facilities<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;The needs of both established and emerging markets - existing situations and prospective new ventures<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Identifying and analysing competitors, trends and opportunities and how to apply best retailing practices and give appropriate focus to customers<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Business principles to help review and create successful investment, marketing and sales strategies and operating policies<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Emerging global obligations and best practices regarding health, safety and environmental issues</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY ONE<br />\r\n	Understanding the Petroleum Products Retail Market<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;What are its attractions?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;What type of business should you be in and why?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Who are the customers?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Who are the competitors?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;What can be learned from the experiences of others?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;How is performance best measured?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Are rewards commensurate with risks?<br />\r\n	Brand Management<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;What is a brand position and why is it essential?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;How is it best conveyed to secure maximum effect?</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY TWO<br />\r\n	Asset Management (Networks)<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;What is the optimum productivity level?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Supply chain management (wet and dry goods)<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;What forms of ownership and property management are available?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;What outlet operating modes should be considered?<br />\r\n	Asset Management (Outlets)<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Principal design considerations<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Customer facilities, health, safety and environmental issues<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Technological aspects of successful retailing<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;How to ensure assets are -sweated&quot; to secure best returns on capital<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;The key onsite features of &quot;retailing for profit&quot;<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;What is the worth of competitive pricing, premium pricing and promotions?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;The identification of customer needs and the prospects for &quot;one stop replenishment&quot;.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY THREE<br />\r\n	Technology<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;What are the latest systems available for complete business management?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;What are the pros and cons regarding electronic funds transfers, and other forms of customer payment?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Loyalty cards and customer information management.<br />\r\n	Site Facilities<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Fuels: what is in prospect for new and advanced products?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Shops: how can full advantage be taken of the opportunity - professionally?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Car care/ car washing: how can poor and mediocre operators become successful?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;What other new business streams or products may be suitable for the retail oil industry?</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	DAY FOUR<br />\r\n	Performance Management<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Performance management: what does it mean, how does it work?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Project management, how its principles can benefit much of the industry-s work<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Regulatory matters, particularly health, safety and environment; what obligations does the industry have to face now and in the foreseeable future?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Inventory management (wet and dry stock) - understand the basics of good supply chain management<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Taking over and handling over sites - manage these key processes reliably.<br />\r\n	DAY FIVE<br />\r\n	General<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;The essentials of good customer relations management - manage resources in ways that will help single out a site as the one of preferred choice from customers&rsquo; points of view<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;On-site crime, how might it be reduced?<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Managing change<br />\r\n	&bull;&nbsp;Concentration on the &quot;must do wells&quot;.</p>\r\n', 'April 22, 2013', 'April 26, 2013', '', 'NGN140,000.00 Vat Inclusive', '2013-04-22', 721, '6', 'December 29, 2012', 1, 0, '', '');
