(140, 'MANAGING PEOPLE FOR STRATEGIC ADVANTAGE (HR SKILLS FOR NON-HR MANAGERS)', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n	This programme exposes Line Managers and Managers in staff functions other than the core HR professionals to the Human Resources concepts that affect their individual business performance. With this course, they will know how the human elements help them to take better strategic decisions. They will also be able to strengthen the employee relationship within their responsibility areas as within the organization as whole. The greatest asset any organisation can have is staff that diplays the best competence at all times.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Programme Objectives</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	At the end of the programme, participants will be able to:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Understand the strategic approach employed by professional human resources managers</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Harness quality staff and align the employees efficiently</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Focus the whole staff on common business goals</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Play their roles in attracting, retaining and deploying the right professionals to achieve group vision.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Develop key business and behaviour skills&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Practice how to link daily activities of their subordinates with set business direction&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Learn how to recognise, stimulate and develop high professional qualities in others</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Ma