(147, 'GUIDES TO SETTING UP A NEW HR DEPARTMENT', '<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n	This course provides the information HR officers need to establish a human resource function in new, small and medium size companies or companies opening an HR department for the first time. It treats matters relating to HR policies, guidelines, procedures, records and information.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY ONE</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Roles of the HR professional</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Operational and Strategic</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Partnering and Policing</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Qualitative and Quantitative</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Short term and Long term.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;Recruiting, Selection and Deployment Processes</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Personnel requisition</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Recruitment procedures</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>New employee orientation</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Deployment.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY TWO</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Personnel Recordkeeping</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Information to include in employee file</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Regulatory compliance</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Payroll</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </spa