ion</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Accident and injury reporting.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n', 'September 3, 2013', 'September 6, 2013', '', 'NGN120,000.00 Vat Inclusive', '2013-09-03', 436, '4', 'January 12, 2013', 1, 0, '', ''),
(150, 'KEY-ACCOUNT MANAGERS TRAINING', '<p>\r\n	Key-Account Managers Training teaches participants the relevant marketing, selling and relational skills needed today to grow and keep an Account for life. Managers of Key Accounts should ever be so vigilant not to &ldquo;supply ammunitions to competitors&rdquo; because in every forward looking company, its Key Accounts are &ldquo;tangible external assets&rdquo; and &ldquo;partners for profit&rdquo; to the Company. For your assets to continue to yield maximally, it must be effectively and efficiently managed. If indeed &ldquo;80%&rdquo; of our current business comes from &ldquo;20%&rdquo; of our Key Accounts, they need to be strategically managed for better returns. If losing an account is &ldquo;very painful&rdquo;, that account must be a key account. We must, therefore, manage the account like an Asset.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Contents</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Day One</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Defining and Identifying Your Key Account</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Why a Key Account is Important</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Why a Key Account is Different</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; What can Make You a Successful Key-Account Manager:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; From the organisation&rsquo;s perspective</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; From personal perspective</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; Skills and qualities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; A Key Account Manager as a Business Partner:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; Climbing the customer perception ladder</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Day Two</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Discovering Business Opportunities:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;&nbsp; Opportunities galore</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;&nbsp; Sales information</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; Prioritising the opportunities</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Key Account Development Plan:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;&nbsp; Setting Key Account objectives</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;&nbsp; Key Account strategies:</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; Tactics to block real or potential competitors</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Managing the Key Account Relationship:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;&nbsp; Increasing the relevant influence</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;&nbsp; Understanding the decision making process</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;&nbsp; Identifying the customer internal politics</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;&nbsp; Contact and networking plan</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Day Three</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Solution Selling</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Communication Acumen:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; Presentation skills</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; Negotiation skills</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; Communications programme and functions</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; Crafting the right messages</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; Employing the appropriate tools</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; Essentials of careful timing of communications</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Internal Capabilities and Support:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; Getting organised</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; Working as a team</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp; Account meetings</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'January 29, 2014', 'January 31, 2014', '', 'NGN100,000.00 VAT INCLUSIVE', '2014-01-29', 333, '10', 'December 3, 2013', 1, 0, '', ''),
(151, 'A MANAGERS PERSONAL EFFECTIVENESS', '<p>\r\n	This course is about what managers can do specifically to improve their individual effectiveness and enhance productivity for the organisation. The programme contents have been developed around seven &ldquo;Key Questions&rdquo; which managers must continually answer for themselves. The questions are:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	What have I been hired to do?</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	What results are expected of me?</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	What can I do to make a real difference in the organisation&rsquo;s fortunes?</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	What are my bosses&rsquo; Critical Result Areas?</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	What Critical Result Areas should be for my sub-ordinates?</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	What do I value most in my life?</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	What do I want to achieve - my goals: Long term? Short-term? Professionally? Socially?</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Contents</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Day One</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Planning Orientation</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The discipline of planning and preparation to avoid unplanned catastrophes: short term planning: daily/weekly/monthly long term planning: self development outlook. Recognise and take full advantage of limited resources.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Focus awareness on company procedures. Time discipline.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Business Knowledge</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Strong knowledge of the organisation&rsquo;s business.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Appreciation of their decisions and actions which touch the business&rsquo;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	bottom line.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Application of competence to see jobs delivered cost effectively.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Performance Orientation</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Focus on delivering results - work efficiently and creatively to meet</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	agreed goals and objectives.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Define personal responsibilities.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Be clear about standards.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Review self performance against set goals.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Opportunities Focused</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Understand what opportunities exist or can be created, and convert them into results.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Take advantage of opportunities for success in the present or future.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Create new ways of doing things that are beneficial, advantageous or profitable.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Problem Solving</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Identify forms of waste to reduce losses.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Make adjustments to accommodate changing situations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Respond resourcefully to new demands or circumstances.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Day Two</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Innovativeness</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Experiment and be adventurous.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Develop new thinking and skills and challenge yourself.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Initiative</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Anticipate business needs to proactively create solutions.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Take on difficult tasks in order to achieve business results.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Delegation and Empowerment</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Willingly delegate.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Provide subordinates with opportunities to prove their capabilities.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Assign the appropriate degree of authority.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Provide assistance and support.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Champion Relevant Changes</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Strive for learning and growth. Structure process for quality and efficiency.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Developing Self</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Strive for learning and growth both professionally and personally.</p>\r\n', 'January 30, 2014', 'January 31, 2014', '', 'NGN80,000.00', '2014-01-30', 309, '4', 'December 3, 2013', 1, 0, '', ''),
(152, 'EXCELLENT REPORT AND PROPOSAL WRITING SKILLS', '<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	For effectiveness in business communications, this course focuses on making managers to:</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&middot; Become highly skilled in the use of English Language</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&middot; Write memos, letters, reports, proposals excellently by presenting their contents with mechanical precision</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&middot; Organise their thoughts clearly before writing</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&middot; Know the techniques of outlining, drafting and revising their written messages</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&middot; Practice writing styles that are clear, concrete and courteous</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&middot; Pay attention to their spellings and punctuations</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&middot; Know the rules that guide the use of numerals in their written messages.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	<strong>Contents</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	Day One</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	<strong>The Challenge of Communicating Effectively</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&middot; The business case</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&middot; Communication and culture.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	<strong>Writing Guidelines</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&middot; Essence of effective business writing</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&middot; Planning the writing</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&middot; Organising thought before writing.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	<strong>Prewriting &amp; Planning</strong></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&middot; Establishing purpose</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">\r\n	&middot; 