(154, 'OCCUPATIONAL HEALTH AND SAFETY MANAGEMENT', '<p>\r\n	Failure to put SMART health, safety and environmental policies and procedures in place could be an expensive mistake. The illnesses and accidents risked as a result could bring a range of costs, including:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; The wages of the person who is injured or ill</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; The costs of covering their job</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Lost productivity caused by inexperienced replacements and disruption to business</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Damage to products, equipment or premises</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Costs of investigating and correcting the problem</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Fines and legal costs if there is a prosecution</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Cost of revamping damaged corporate image</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Contents</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Day One</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Introduction to safety at work</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Risk assessment</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Accident concepts</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Implementation of health and safety in projects</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Accident investigation and reporting</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; HSE Management System (including OHSAS 18001:2007) and its implementation</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Hazard identification and control</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Application of job hazard analysis</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; First Aid and CPR</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Fire Safety Management</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Day Two</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Implementing OSH management system for success</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Injuries: a matter of probabilities</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; HSE calculations</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; HSE performance indicators</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Loss Time Injury Frequency (LTIF)</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Understanding workplace ergonomics</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Workplace interactions</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Ergonomic risk factors</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; MSDs and other common problems</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&middot; Ergonomics of co