(191, 'COMPETENCIES IN SERVICE STRATEGY', '<div>\r\n	<strong>Programme Description</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	A customer service thought process that enables everyone participating in it to contribute to development of strategies regarding:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Understanding Customer Equity:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Customer value proposition</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Customer bonding</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Customer mind-share</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>What is changing in the business.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Where opportunities and options exist for the competence enhancement.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Agreement on service targets and specific actions.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Contents</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY ONE</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>The Customer Perspective in the Balanced Scorecard</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>The preliminary questions:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Who are the customers?</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Who&rsquo;s bothered about service penalties?</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Personal Attitudes and Customer Service Experience</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Understanding the Eight Customer Types</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Giving Random Experience</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Giving Predictable Experience.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY TWO