(229, 'INVENTORY, LOGISTICS & DISTRIBUTION MANAGEMENT', '<div>\r\n	<strong>Programme description</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Logistics has become a quintessential factor in modern day organisations. This course examines the core issues and skills required to promote production and distribution efficiency, reduce waste and consequently improving Return on Investment (ROI). &nbsp;The programme will afford the personnel in Logistics to be on top of their assignments.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Contents</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY ONE</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Inventory Management</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Introduction to basic concepts in storekeeping</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Types of Inventory (RM, WIP, FP, MRO)</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Inventory Planning and Control</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Stores Accounting and Stock-taking</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Materials Handling Techniques</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY TWO</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Distribution/Logistics Management</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Organisation and Management of the Warehouse, Customer Service</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Distribution Planning and Transport Operations &amp; Management</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Impact of Stores/Warehousing Operations on Organisational Efficiency and Profitability</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Good Housekeeping Practices</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY THREE</div>\r\n