(230, 'MANAGERIAL SKILLS APPRECIATION (FIRST LEVEL MANAGERS PROGRAMME)', '<div>\r\n	<strong>Objectives</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	This course is to introduce first level managers to office and business management by making them</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Understand their roles within the changes that do affect business</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Get clear the management styles that can affect their success</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Develop the right competencies in the work environment, with their boss and also with peers and subordinates</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Maintain necessary discipline at work</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Know how their career can grow.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Contents</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY ONE</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>What Management is, What Process is.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Who is a manager?</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Levels of Management</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;First Line Skills</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Middle Line Skills</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Top Line Skills</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Managerial roles</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Interpersonal</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Informational</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Decisional</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Managerial Functions</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &n