(239, 'TRAINING MANAGERS TO TRAIN - CLASSROOM TRAINING DELIVERY SKILLS', '<div>\r\n	<strong>Programme Description</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	This course provides managers and instructors with knowledge and skills to design and facilitate learning in a classroom environment. Participants in this course will experience and practice the full range of skills needed to deliver a training session effectively.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	By the end of it they will:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Find their training skills as a whole substantially upgraded.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Master particular delivery techniques that can help to transfer difficult technical knowledge enthusiastically to others.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Be able to prepare their lessons and teaching aids adequately using a systematic planning approach.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Know how to structure the content of their training most effectively.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Master the verbal and non-verbal styles of expression to affect the attention and assimilation of class members.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Be able to manage their time and also handle questions efficiently during their teaching sessions.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Contents</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY ONE</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Symptoms of the existence of Training Needs</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Training defined</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Adult Learning Process</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbs