(246, 'SPEECHWRITING COURSE', '<div>\r\n	<strong>Programme Description</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	In today&#39;s work environment, a special selection of managers in corporate, government and the non-profit organisations are tasked with crafting good speeches, often at a moment&#39;s notice.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	This course will provide a hands-on, detailed lesson in the art of speechwriting, including what works and what doesn&#39;t, how to make points clearly and maintain the audience&rsquo;s interest. &nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	In addition to the essentials, participants will learn techniques for composing speeches that engage, persuade and inspire through the use of image, metaphor, and story-telling.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Participants will analyse some of the greatest speeches to determine what makes them effective and memorable.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Specific Benefits</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Individual managers who participate in the programme will:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Master the skills with which they can write speeches that transfer valuable policy, business and technical information enthusiastically to other persons.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Learn the art of preparing adequately for their written speeches using a systematic planning approach.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Know how to structure the contents of the speech most effectively</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Master the language expressions to affect the assimilation of the audience to which the speech is being presented</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Manage their writing time effectively.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Contents</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY ONE</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Kinds of Speech</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Informative</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Persuasive</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Inspirational.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Anatomy of a Great Written Speech</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>A review of sample great speeches in history</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Clear about the goal the speaker is to achieve</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Resonates &ldquo;What&rsquo;s In It for Me&rdquo; to the audience</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>In tune with the speaker&rsquo;s voice</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Simple in words</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Original</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Authentic.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	The Speechwriter&rsquo;s Tool Kit</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Facts researching</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Dictionary</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Biographies</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Great speeches</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Quotations.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Between the Speechwriter and the Presenter</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Strong bonding</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Sense of identity</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Mutual belief.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY TWO</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Speechwriting Steps&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Meeting with the executives</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Deciding the theme</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Reviewing the audience</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Agreeing the slant&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Speechwriting Process</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Deciding the topic</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Understanding the audience</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Researching - information and data gathering</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Setting the speech framework</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Deciding the significant points to address&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Agreeing the Executive&rsquo;s (speech presenter&rsquo;s) perspective or position on the significant points&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Agreeing the executive&rsquo;s (speech presenter&rsquo;s) preferred style</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Identifying ways to effectively capture a speaker&#39;s voice</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Identifying ways to use speechwriting to successfully convey a message or a policy</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Building a speech around a strong proposition</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Writing openings that grab an audience&rsquo;s attention&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Closings that stick in an audience memory</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Using stories to bring ideas to life.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY THREE</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Doing the Writing</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Organising thought before writing</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Writing for the ear</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Word usage</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Common errors in the use of English by Nigerians</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Preparing the draft</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Presenting the draft</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Revising or making changes to the draft as presenter may request</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Word economy</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Rhetorical techniques that engage and persuade the audience&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Style and tone</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Paragraphs</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Headings.</div>\