(272, 'KEY-ACCOUNT MANAGERS TRAINING', '<div>\r\n	<strong>Justifying the Programme</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Key-Account Managers Training teaches participants the relevant marketing, selling and relational skills needed today to grow and keep an Account for life. Managers of Key Accounts should ever be so vigilant not to &ldquo;supply ammunitions to competitors&rdquo; because in every forward looking company, its Key Accounts are &ldquo;tangible external assets&rdquo; and &ldquo;partners for profit&rdquo; to the Company.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	For your assets to continue to yield maximally, it must be effectively and efficiently managed. If indeed &ldquo;80%&rdquo; of our current business comes from &ldquo;20%&rdquo; of our Key Accounts, they need to be strategically managed for better returns. If losing an account is &ldquo;very painful&rdquo;, that account must be a key account. We must, therefore, manage the account like an Asset.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Contents</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY ONE</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Defining and Identifying Your Key Account</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Why a Key Account is Important</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Why a Key Account is Different</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>What Can Make You a Successful Key-Account Manager:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;From the organisation&rsquo;s perspective</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;From personal perspective</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Skills and qualities</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>A Key Account Manager as a Business Partner:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Climbing the customer perception ladder</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY TWO</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Discovering Business Opportunities:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Opportunities galore</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Sales information</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Prioritising the opportunities</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Key Account Development Plan:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Setting Key Account objectives</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Key Account strategies:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Tactics to block real or potential competitors</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Managing the Key Account Relationship:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Increasing the relevant influence</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Understanding the decision making process</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Identifying the customer internal politics</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Contact and networking plan</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY THREE</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Solution Selling</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Communication Acumen:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Presentation skills</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Negotiation skills</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Communications programme and functions</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Crafting the right messages</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Employing the appropriate tools&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp; &nbsp; o &nbsp;Essentials of careful timing of communications&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Internal Capabilities and Support:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp