(276, 'OCCUPATIONAL HEALTH AND SAFETY MANAGEMENT', '<div>\r\n	<strong>Focus of the Course</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Failure to put SMART health, safety and environmental policies and procedures in place could be an expensive mistake. &nbsp;The illnesses and accidents risked as a result could bring a range of costs, including:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>The wages of the person who is injured or ill</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>The costs of covering their job</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Lost productivity caused by inexperienced replacements and disruption to business</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Damage to products, equipment or premises</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Costs of investigating and correcting the problem</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Fines and legal costs if there is a prosecution</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Cost of revamping damaged corporate image</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Contents</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY ONE</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Introduction to safety at work</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Risk assessment</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Accident concepts</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Implementation of health and safety in projects</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Accident investigation and reporting</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>HSE Management System (including OHSAS 18001:2007) and its implementation</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Hazard identification and control</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Application of job hazard analysis</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>First Aid and CPR</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Fire Safety Management</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY TWO</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Implementing OSH management system for success</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Injuries: a matter of probabilities</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>HSE calculations</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>HSE performance indicators</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Loss Time Injury Frequency (LTIF)</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Understanding workplace ergonomics</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Workplace interactions</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Ergonomic risk factors</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>MSDs and other common problems</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Ergonomics of computer usage</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Techniques of Lifting of weights</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n', 'May 22, 2014', 'May 23, 2014', '', 'NGN80,000 VAT INCLUSIVE',