(278, 'PROBLEM SOLVING AND DECISION MAKING TECHNIQUES', '<div>\r\n	<strong>Programme Description</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	This programme delivers Problem Solving Techniques, one of the unique competencies all managers, whether budding or experienced, must possess.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	The ability of a manager to solve problems will be reflected in:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Gathering information</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Marshaling relevant resources</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Weighing options</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Assessing risks</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Taking decisive action.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>What the Participants will Learn</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Definitions and data collection for various workplace problems</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Root Cause analysis</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Crisis investigation, recovery and prevention procedures</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Process for documenting solutions and decisions</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Character and techniques needed for making value-laden decisions.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Contents</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY ONE</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Three things people do when faced with problems</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Generic skil