(296, 'GROWING DISTRIBUTION CHANNELS EFFECTIVELY', '<div>\r\n	<strong>Programme Description</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	Channels must be managed in a coherent manner if the business will achieve increased profitability. &nbsp;This programme will address the skill improvement and tool sharpening requirements of sales and marketing managers so as to improve overall management of distribution.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Goals the Training Will Attain</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	During this programme, participants will learn to:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Identify the strategic role distribution management plays in company&rsquo;s business models.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Segment the market for optimal and profitable distribution design</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Identify gaps in outlets performances</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Bring about productive change in channels operations</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Effectively identify conflicts and develop effective tools for resolving them.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Contents</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY ONE</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Issues to consider in a channel of distribution</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Issues that are critical to effective channel coordination</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Optimising dealership and retail structures to meet the end users&rsquo; demands.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Issues that affect intensity of distribution</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Allocating Resources to Channel Members</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Assessing Demand Side/Supply Side Gaps in the Current Strategy</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Analysing The Channel Gaps</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Distinguishing The Demand Side and Supply Side Gaps</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Effective Tools to Address the Gaps</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	DAY TWO</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Wholesale and Retail Coordination</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Designing Healthy Competitive Programmes for the Wholesalers and Retailers</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Harmonising The Goals of the Different Channel Members</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Providing Adequate Knowledge to and Motivating Wholesalers and Retailers</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Channel Conflict Management</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Types of Channels Conflict</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Tools for Effective Channel Conflict Management</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Influencing Channel Members Behaviour</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Antecedents Behaviour and Rewards System</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Sources of Power and Its Us