(306, 'SKILLFUL BUSINESS NEGOTIATIONS - THE PRINCIPLES AND PRACTICE', '<div>\r\n	<strong>Programme Description</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	A training programme whose contents have been developed around six &ldquo;Key Negotiation Lessons,&rdquo; namely:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Avoid unreasonable or arbitrary positions</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Avoid letting prejudices show through</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Avoid negotiating by demands and ultimatums</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Present arguments calmly, without personalizing</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Explain positions logically and frankly</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Recognise legitimate concerns and needs of other side.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	<strong>Broad Competencies Addressed</strong></div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Ability to assess one&rsquo;s central negotiating style &ndash; collaborate, compromise, defeat, withdraw or accommodate.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Ability to assess one&rsquo;s true power in any negotiation process</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Ability to concede without losing out</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Ability to employ any of the several tactics negotiators use and manage when any of the tactics are being tried by other parties</div>\r\n<div>\r\n	&bull;<span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space:pre"> </span>Ability to assess a true crisis situation and not a contrived one, so as to employ the