(308, 'STRATEGIC FINANCIAL PLANNING, CONTROL & EVALUATION FOR PROJECTS', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Programme Description</strong><br />\r\n	Projects are different from normal operational activity of an organization, while having the same principles of finance the context and content varies. Strategic financial planning for projects can be simply described s a process of determining a project&rsquo;s financial goals, and priorities. After considering the resources available and how to acquire them, a risk profile is determined and subsequently to detail a balanced and realistic plan to meet those goals. The project goals are used as a guideposts to map a course of action on what needs to be done to meet those goals.<br />\r\n	Alongside the data gathering exercise, the purpose of each goal is determined to ensure that the goal is meaningful in the context of the projects situation. Through a process of careful analysis, these goals are subjected to a reality check by considering the projects current and future resources available to achieve them.<br />\r\n	In the process, the constraints and obstacles to these goals are noted. The information will be used later to determine if there are sufficient resources available to meet these goals and what other things need to be considered in the process. If the resources are insufficient or absent to meet these goals the particular goals will be adjusted to a more realistic level or will be replaced with a new goal.<br />\r\n	Financial planning should cover all areas of the projects financial needs and should result in the achievement of the goal of the project.<br />\r\n	Programme<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	<strong>Course Content</strong><br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Strategic management and project selection<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project manager and organization<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project planning<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project budgeting and cost estimation<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scheduling and time tracking systems<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Resource allocation &ndash; financial planning<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project finance<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Financial resources control<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Current asset controls<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Stock control<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Purchasing methods<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Monitoring and information systems<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Planning, monitoring and controlling cycle<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Information needs and the reporting process<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Earned value analysis<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project control<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project management modules and simulation<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Work study<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Time charts<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Crisis management and disaster planning<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Capital expenditure analysis<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Investment decision process<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Capital budgeting process<br />\r\n	<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cost of capital<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Risk management and insurance planning<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tax planning<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cash flow management<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project auditing<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Post project review<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Project termination<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Managing Business task<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Managing performance<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Business excellence model<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Staff planning<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Final report<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Global financial environment<br />\r\n	&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Review and outlook</p>\r\n', 'July 22, 2014', 'July 25, 2014', '', 'NGN120,000 VAT INCLUSIVE', '2014-07-22', 113, '10', 'July 10, 2014', 1, 0, '', ''),
(309, 'BEST PRACTICES IN DOCUMENTS, ARCHIVES AND RECORDS MANAGEMENT', '<p><strong>DESIGNED FOR:</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\nMiddle and Senior Level Officers.&nbsp; Administrative Staffs, Document Controllers, Registers and Archivists.<br />\r\n<strong>OBJECTIVES</strong><br />\r\nParticipants should be able to do the following upon completion of the course:<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manage /control documents, including folders and forms reduce document distribution costs &ndash; no more paper.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Explain the primary tools used for identifying records.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Appraisal principles and technique.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Archival theory and practice.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;To understand document and records management life cycle.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Understand ISO 15489 records management standard.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Review how to implement a records management system based&nbsp; on ISO 15489<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Create a document and records management plan of action to implement in their organization and learn from best practice implementations and case studies.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Learn about legislation, standards and regulation.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Set up search and retrieval.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Setting up access controls and security.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Develop storage models, audit trail and storage technologies.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Explain the need for vital records protection and disaster recovery planning.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Identify factors that help reduce the area and time of a records search.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Archive document using principles of Original Order and Provenance.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; Prepared finding Aids</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PROGRAMME CONTENT</strong><br />\r\nIntroduction: &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Course Objectives and Outline<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;EDMS &ndash; what is it and benefits<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The paper flood<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The paperless Office<br />\r\nEDMS COMPONENTS AND DOCUMENT CAPTURE, DISTRIBUTION AND BROWSING<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Scanning of documents<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;OCR and image processing<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Demonstration<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Indexing, archiving and retrieval<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Document capture<br />\r\nSTRATEGY AND UNDERSTANDING KEY ELEMENTS<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Document and records management strategy<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Information governance<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Understanding the terminology<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Managing Information assets<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;ISO 15489<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;ISO 5489 Part 1 and Part 2 overview<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Introduce document an records management<br />\r\n&nbsp;PAPER RECORDS PROCESSING SYSTEM<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Explain the role of paper desk organization in records management.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Outline the options in the paper&nbsp; and email route<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Assess the efficiency of their departments&rsquo; current information storage and filing system<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Describe classification, cross references and index systems for paper based storage.<br />\r\nCONCEPTS AND SET UP COMPONENTS<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Classification schemes<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Searching and retrieving<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Controls and security<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Metadata and indexing<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Document and records lifecycle<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Capture, store and management<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Preserve and archive<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Presentation and delivery<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;legislation, standards and regulation<br />\r\nOTHER SOURCES OF DOCUMENTS<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Word processors/spreadsheets<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Forms<br />\r\nDOCUMENT MANAGEMENT<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Document control<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Revisions/versions/histories<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Audit trails<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Reports<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Demonstration<br />\r\n<br />\r\nFORMS MANAGEMENT<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Creating forms<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Filling and saving forms/data<br />\r\nDOCUMENT DISTRIBUTION: Work Flow Management<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Applications<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Creations<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Tracking/closure<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Demonstration<br />\r\nDOCUMENT DISTRIBUTION:&nbsp; Electronic Mail<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Concepts<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Demonstration<br />\r\nDOCUMENT BROWING<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Navigation<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Application/independent viewers<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Annotation/sticky/notes/red/lining<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Demonstration<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;ISO 9000 and other regulatory requirement<br />\r\nSYSTEM ARCHITECTURES AND PLATFORMS.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;LAN&rsquo;s and WANs<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Client server architectures<br />\r\nTECHNOLOGY OPTION<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Authoring system<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Card/folio based system<br />\r\nEMERGING STANDARDS IN EDMS:&nbsp; Types of documentation system.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;On-line help system<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;On-line coaches and tutorials<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;On-line documentation<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Glossaries<br />\r\nSOME REPRESENTATIVE EDMS PRODUCTS<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Implementing EDMS<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Off &ndash; the self vs. customs systems<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Allocating resources<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;EDMS management<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Updating system<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Future topics<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Documents on demand<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Multimedia documents&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>RATIONAL</strong><br />\r\nShould records be stored on paper, in an electronic format, in a microform? How is a records inventory conducted? What are the steps in the development of an organization-wide Records retention schedule?&nbsp; How are records archived?&nbsp; This course will assist you in making those decisions based upon certain characteristics of the records.&nbsp; Also the rules established by the Association of Records Managers and Administrators (ARMA) will be used for the proper coding and filing of records.&nbsp; It is about attaining a records management benchmark of best practice, setting up methodology, processes and the resulting data storage and using an electronic records management system.&nbsp; This course shows you how to deal with papers in an electronic way to get rid of the papers hard copy which takes a lot of space and time.&nbsp; Managing documents and content can be difficult.&nbsp; How best do you store and mange the documents and records in your organization?&nbsp; Does your approach meet compliance requirements, regulations and standards?&nbsp;&nbsp; What is the best way to manage electronic documents and records?&nbsp; How do you find the right documents and records when you need them?&nbsp; How does workflow and business management work with documents and records management to help increase efficiency within your organization? &nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'September 8, 2016', 'December 22, 2016', '11am', 'NGN120,000 VAT INCLUSIVE', '2016-09-08', 170, '8', 'July 10, 2014', 1, 19, 'Kaduna', ''),
(310, 'AGGRESSIVE MARKET PENETRATION (BATTLES FOR MARKET SHARE)', '<p><strong>Programme Description</strong><br />\r\nA four-day sales and marketing training on intense and offensive market drive.&nbsp; With speed, the sales and marketing persons must:<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;generate awareness for the company&rsquo;s products<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;achieve visibility in trade and outlets &ndash; wholesalers and distributors, retailers<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;maximise volume delivery and achieve company&rsquo;s objectives fast<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;grow market share for the brands.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Broad Competencies Addressed</strong><br />\r\n1.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Initiate more contacts and form strong relationships.<br />\r\n2.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Qualify prospects by performing analysis on what, when, and under what conditions they will buy.<br />\r\n3.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Effectively apply sales literature, promotions, tactics and offers for specific new transactions with individual prospects.<br />\r\n4.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Influence sales outlets by building value and encourage them to believe in the company&rsquo;s brands.<br />\r\n5.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Effectively manage resistance from difficult prospects so as to make successful sales.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Contents<br />\r\nDAY ONE</strong><br />\r\nPersonal Selling Skills<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Probing skills<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Objections handling<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;How well you know the customer<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Sales challenges and sales differentiators<br />\r\n<br />\r\nImplementing the Sales Strategy<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Planning the Market Prospecting:<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Develop the right objectives<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Identify customers&#39; real interests<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Prioritise the customers.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDeveloping the Major Accounts<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Qualifying Customers - Criteria for Prioritising:<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Potential size of account<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;History of patronage<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Previous relationship on other platforms<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Pressing need for product/service<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Clear cost-benefit relationship - positive attitude<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Financial soundness of the customer<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Customer accessibility.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>DAY TWO</strong><br />\r\nOutlets Management<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Territory Management:<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;territory delineation<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;route planning<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;the Selling Process &ndash; Call Plans<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;sales target for the period<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;merchandising<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;other objectives for the period<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;adding new prospects and deleting &ldquo;dogs&rdquo;.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nRelationship Management Competencies<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Offer Analysis:<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Customer benefits<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;What&rsquo;s special about you &ndash; the Appeal<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>DAY THREE</strong><br />\r\nProfitable Negotiation<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Rules of Commercial Negotiation:<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;No negotiation when selling is unsure<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Increase level of customer needs first<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Concession strategies<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Common Negotiation Tactics:<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Bogey<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Good guy, Bad guy<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Nibbling<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Crunch<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>DAY FOUR</strong><br />\r\nMerchandising<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Checking the store rooms for stocks<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Maximising on-shelf availability and product visibility<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Effective product placement.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&ldquo;Brain Sell&rdquo;<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;How the salespersons&rsquo; mental agility can increase so as to perform at the very best<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;How to bring high energy to bear for top performance<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;How the salespersons can identify their individual personal strengths and weaknesses and plan for self-development<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;How to analyse the motivations and priorities of key buying influences.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'June 15, 2016', 'July 10, 2016', '11am', 'NGN120,000.00 Vat Inclusive', '2016-06-15', 226, '6', 'August 7, 2014', 1, 28, 'Abeokuta', ''),
(311, 'SITUATIONAL LEADERSHIP PROGRAMME - LEADERSHIP COMPETENCIES DEVELOPMENT TRAINING', '<p><strong>Programme Description</strong><br />\nSituational Leadership Programme supports the building of<br />\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;leader behavioural skills<br />\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;business knowledge<br />\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;the right vision of life<br />\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;growth of subordinates.<br />\nFor each participant, the programme answers the question:<br />\n&ldquo;What do I need to know and do to be an effective<br />\nLeader that inspires other employees, thinks not as<br />\na job holder but as one assuming responsibilities?&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n<strong>Contents</strong><br />\n<strong>DAY ONE</strong><br />\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The four leadership pillars:<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Choose the leadership styles that are appropriate under different circumstances for delivering desired results.<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Motivate, coach and develop others.<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Maximise business opportunities.<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Support/Build shared vision.<br />\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Leadership as Influence:<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Understand leadership powers<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Focus on emerging situations<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Take charge in new situations<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Lead effective change<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Maintain self confidence<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Maintain constructive relationship<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Take initiative to make things better<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Lead by example.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>DAY TWO</strong><br />\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Personality Types and Behavioural Motivations:<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Promoting or Expressive personality type<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Controlling personality type<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Analysing personality type<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Supporting or Amiable personality type.<br />\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Leadership Styles:<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Choose communication styles that are appropriate:<br />\n- Telling, Selling, Participating, Delegating<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Plan and prioritise daily activities<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Decide when to manage, decide when to lead<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Get and use appropriate Feedback<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Have a coach or mentor<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Be a coach or mentor to someone.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>DAY THREE</strong><br />\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Conflict Management Styles:<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Collaborate<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Compromise<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Defeat<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Accommodate<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Withdraw.<br />\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Deliver Results:<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Use performance measurement to assess the effectiveness of leading others<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Lead teams in terms of their major contributions and how they fit into the larger organisation picture<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Mutually identify priorities, necessary skills and guidelines<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Set milestones for progress review.<br />\n<br />\n<strong>DAY FOUR</strong><br />\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Profile the Organisation:<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Organisation culture<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The 4+2 formula<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Business choice<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Business phases and leadership creativity<br />\n&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;One right answer?<br />\n&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Self imposed barrier?<br />\n&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Conformity?<br />\n&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Impatience?<br />\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Rules of Work:<br />\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Do you know what it takes to keep top jobs?<br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n', 'July 14, 2016', 'July 20, 2016', '10am', 'NGN120,000 VAT INCLUSIVE', '2016-07-14', 103, '5', 'August 20, 2014', 1, 14, 'Ile-Ogbo', ''),
