n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Leadership Styles:<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Choose communication styles that are appropriate:<br />\r\n- Telling, Selling, Participating, Delegating<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Plan and prioritise daily activities<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Decide when to manage, decide when to lead<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Get and use appropriate Feedback<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Have a coach or mentor<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Be a coach or mentor to someone.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>DAY THREE</strong><br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Conflict Management Styles:<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Collaborate<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Compromise<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Defeat<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Accommodate<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Withdraw.<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Deliver Results:<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Use performance measurement to assess the effectiveness of leading others<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Lead teams in terms of their major contributions and how they fit into the larger organisation picture<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Mutually identify priorities, necessary skills and guidelines<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Set milestones for progress review.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>DAY FOUR</strong><br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Profile the Organisation:<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Organisation culture<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The 4+2 formula<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Business choice<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Business phases and leadership creativity<br />\r\n&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;One right answer?<br />\r\n&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Self imposed barrier?<br />\r\n&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Conformity?<br />\r\n&ndash;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Impatience?<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Rules of Work:<br />\r\no&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Do you know what it takes to keep top jobs?<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'April 29, 2016', 'May 7, 2016', '11am', '234', '2016-04-29', 0, '5', 'April 22, 2016', 1, 12, 'Ketu', '832157_course_with_image_11.jpe'),
(312, 'A MANAGERS PERSONAL EFFECTIVENESS', '<p><strong>Programme Description</strong><br />\r\nThis course is about what managers can do specifically to improve their individual effectiveness and enhance productivity for the organisation. The programme contents have been developed around seven &ldquo;Key Questions&rdquo; which managers must continually answer for themselves. The questions are:<br />\r\n&bull; What have I been hired to do?<br />\r\n&bull; What results are expected of me?<br />\r\n&bull; What can I do to make a real difference in the organisation&rsquo;s fortunes?<br />\r\n&bull; What are my bosses&rsquo; Critical Result Areas?<br />\r\n&bull; What Critical Result Areas should be for my sub-ordinates?<br />\r\n&bull; What do I value most in my life?<br />\r\n&bull; What do I want to achieve - my goals: Long term? Short-term? Professionally? Socially?<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Contents<br />\r\nDAY ONE</strong><br />\r\nPlanning Orientation<br />\r\n&bull; The discipline of planning and preparation to avoid unplanned catastrophes:<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; o&nbsp; short term planning: daily/weekly/monthly<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; o&nbsp; long term planning: self development outlook.<br />\r\n&bull; Recognise and take full advantage of limited resources.<br />\r\n&bull; Focus awareness on company procedures.<br />\r\n&bull; Time discipline.<br />\r\nBusiness Knowledge<br />\r\n&bull; Strong knowledge of the organisation&rsquo;s business.<br />\r\n&bull; Appreciation of their decisions and actions which touch the business&rsquo; bottom line.<br />\r\n&bull; Application of competence to see jobs delivered cost effectively.<br />\r\nPerformance Orientation<br />\r\n&bull; Focus on delivering results - work efficiently and creatively to meet agreed goals and objectives.<br />\r\n&bull; Define personal responsibilities.<br />\r\n&bull; Be clear about standards.<br />\r\n&bull; Review self performance against set goals.<br />\r\nOpportunities Focused<br />\r\n&bull; Understand what opportunities exist or can be created, and convert them into results.<br />\r\n&bull; Take advantage of opportunities for success in the present or future.<br />\r\n&bull; Create new ways of doing things that are beneficial, advantageous or profitable.<br />\r\nProblem Solving<br />\r\n&bull; Identify forms of waste to reduce losses.<br />\r\n&bull; Make adjustments to accommodate changing situations.<br />\r\n&bull; Respond resourcefully to new demands or circumstances.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>DAY TWO</strong><br />\r\nInnovativeness<br />\r\n&bull; Experiment and be adventurous.<br />\r\n&bull; Develop new thinking and skills and challenge yourself.<br />\r\nInitiative<br />\r\n&bull; Anticipate business needs to proactively create solutions.<br />\r\n&bull; Take on difficult tasks in order to achieve business results.<br />\r\nDelegation and Empowerment<br />\r\n&bull; Willingly delegate.<br />\r\n&bull; Provide subordinates with opportunities to prove their capabilities.<br />\r\n&bull; Assign the appropriate degree of authority.<br />\r\n&bull; Provide assistance and support.<br />\r\nChampion Relevant Changes<br />\r\n&bull; Strive for learning and growth.<br />\r\n&bull; Structure process for quality and efficiency.<br />\r\nDeveloping Self<br />\r\n&bull; Strive for learning and growth both professionally and personally.</p>\r\n', 'July 20, 2016', 'August 25, 2016', '3:00pm', 'NGN80,000 VAT INCLUSIVE', '2016-07-20', 52, '9', 'September 25, 2014', 1, 25, 'Ketu', '');
