(6, 'STRATEGY & TACTICS  Information that Matters to Business Strategists and Government Strategists    From TOM ASSOCIATES Training', '<p align="left">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">The Roman Council sent its army into Germana to wipe out rebellions there, overwhelming the poorly armed tribal warriors with archers, cavalry and a large infantry. Three years later, the Council decided that Germana needed a second thrashing and sent its legions back.</span></p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">But the tribes had developed a new strategy. They tactically drew the archers into the woods to block their arrows. They drew the cavalry into swamps to immobilize the horses. They drew the infantry into bogs. (Read </span><em style="font-size: 12px;">CORPS BUSINESS </em><span style="font-size: 12px;">by David Freedman.)</span></p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">Take a break: </span><em style="font-size: 12px;">Can you think of a modern-day parallel experience</em><span style="font-size: 12px;">?</span></p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">Message for Business: </span><em style="font-size: 12px;">The challenges to face tomorrow will not be the same ones faced today. So do not get stuck.</em></p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">Message for Government: </span><em style="font-size: 12px;">Read the book </em><span style="font-size: 12px;">BEATING GOLIATH by Jeffrey Record.</span></p>\r\n<p align="left" style="margin-left:3in;">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">www.tomassociatesng.com</span></p>\r\n', 'November 7, 2013'),
(7, 'COMMON HABITS OF UNSUCESSFUL CHIEF EXECUTIES', '<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\r\n	<strong style="font-size: 12px;">1. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><strong style="font-size: 12px;">They see themselves as dominating.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\r\n	<strong>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>There is no clear boundary between their personal interests and corporate interests.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\r\n	<strong>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>They seem to have all the answers, often dazzling people with the speed and decisiveness with which they can deal with challenging issues.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\r\n	<strong>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>They make sure that everyone is 100 percent behind them, ruthlessly eliminating anyone who they perceive might undermine their efforts.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\r\n	<strong>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>They are consummate managers of their personal image in confusion with their efforts at managing and developing the corporate image.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\r\n	<strong>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>They treat major obstacles as temporary impediments to be removed.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\r\n	<strong>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>They often return to the strategies and tactics that made them get to the level of success they find themselves at.</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>&nbsp;Reference: WHY SMART EXECUTIVES FAIL by Sydney Finkelstein</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>&nbsp; TOM ASSOCIATES Training &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; www.tomassociatesng.com</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n', 'November 11, 2013'),
(8, 'WHAT DO YOUR FEARS LOOK LIKE?', '<p>\r\n	<strong>Here is an information you may find to be of help</strong><strong style="font-size: 12px;"><em style="font-size: 12px;">&nbsp;&ndash; From TOM ASSOCIATES Training</em><em style="font-size: 12px;">.</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>What do your fears look like? What pictures, words, or objects would you use to capture your fears?</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>A construction worker gets busy on a skyscraper. One fellow watches him work sixty meters (about 200 feet) above the ground on the scaffolding arrayed around the outside of the twenty four-storey skyscraper. This fellow feels a nervousness that is making him numb even while standing on the ground &ndash; never mind thinking of climbing up to the construction worker.</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>When the worker climbs down to the ground the fellow asks him whether he ever experiences that queasy dizziness that accompanies fear of heights, even for a moment. &ldquo;If I had, I wouldn&rsquo;t be here in one piece now,&rdquo; the skyscraper worker replies curtly, &ldquo;In fact, I&rsquo;d be dead. For me, that kind of fear would be unreasonable, and unhealthy.&quot;</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Now, just think about the influence of fear on the life of many people &ndash; how it inhibits creativity and infect self-confidence. But contained, fear is incapable of harming or controlling anyone: it stays controlled.</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Failure to attain a goal, failure to realize a dream, unemployment, business failure, homelessness, poor health, dying and heading for &lsquo;hell&rsquo; &ndash; people contemplate such calamity all the time, however remote the possibility they will fall victim of these things. People simply harbour and feed the fear.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Always be conscious of how fear affects performance. Fear paralyzes some people &ndash; not only can&rsquo;t they perform at their best, they become unable to perform at all. However, just check it out: the nervousness speakers &ndash; and</strong>&nbsp;<em><strong>all speakers</strong></em><strong>&nbsp;to be sure &ndash; feel before a public speaking engagement. It is a nervousness that does not need to paralyze them. Rather, experienced speakers use it as an energizer. It turns out to give a blast of adrenaline that translates into an extra jolt of excitement in their speeches. It&rsquo;s true for runners, swimmers, and other sports champions too, just as it is for business people poised on the starting block. The jitters they experience add to their explosive leap towards their goal.</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Fear converted to energy drives us courageously forward, straight towards the thing we&rsquo;re afraid of. It can help in dealing with reality rather than avoiding it. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><em style="font-size: 12px;"><strong>Adapted from</strong></em><strong style="font-size: 12px;">&nbsp;THINK LIKE A GENIUS by Todd Siler</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong style="font-size: 12px;">info@tomassociatesng.com &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; www.tomassociatesng.com</strong></p>\r\n', 'November 18, 2013'),
(9, 'SERVICE FAILURE ?', '<p>\r\n	<strong>This is an information that matters to all Future Leaders &ndash; from TOM ASSOCIATES Training.</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong style="font-size: 12px;">It is a true story, and one that Tom Associates believes you should please share. Forward it to friends and colleagues. All people who would manage service activities successfully must learn from it.</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong style="font-size: 12px;">Characters have been disguised, but if you are a regular reader of <em>The Guardian Life,</em>&nbsp;the weekly magazine accompaniment of&nbsp;<em>The Guardian on Sunday,</em> you could get the clue.</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong style="font-size: 12px;">Here goes. The customer got what to him was a &ldquo;raw deal&rdquo; from his service provider and he published an article about it. Within two days of publishing the story, three senior staff of the service provider company wrote to him. Here are the mails:</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong style="font-size: 12px;">First Letter:</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	<strong><em>Dear Customer,</em></strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\r\n	<strong><em>I read your article on the subject service with a feeling of nostalgia. I assure you of my resolve to look into these and other shortcomings of my organization brought to my knowledge by you and many other customers in recent times. I sincerely regret the inconvenience caused you and many of our valued customers. Thank you for your understanding.</em></strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	<strong>Second Letter:</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	<strong><em>Dear Customer,</em></strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\r\n	<strong><em>First and foremost, thank you for choosing to do business with us. My colleagues and I read your article with great concern. We do appreciate your feedback and comments and it is such feedback that enables us track and to rectify process failures in a growing institution that ours is. To assist us further in making our service greater kindly advice us of your personal details.&nbsp; Hope to hear from you soon. Best regards.</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	<strong>Third Letter:</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	<strong><em>Hello Customer,</em></strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.5in;">\r\n	<strong><em>We refer to your article published recently. We sincerely apologise for any inconveniences caused by this situation. Please be assured that we are working to resolve this issue once and for all. Kindly send us your personal details as well as your telephone numbers to enable us expedite action on your issue. Once again, we are sorry for any inconveniences this might have caused you. Best regards.</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong style="font-size: 12px;">Great, concluded the affected customer. Please note that in two of the three mails, the customer was asked to supply his personal details so his case could be attended to. And here is the mail he sent to the organization&rsquo;s officials in response:</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong style="font-size: 12px;"><em>Hello Good Fellows,</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><em>It is nice to see you react so quickly to my published article. However, I shall not be giving you my personal details or telephone numbers. The reason is simple. If I give my personal details and you solve my problems, what happens to the numerous other people suffering from same bad service but who do not have access to the media and therefore cannot write about this?</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong style="font-size: 12px;"><em>I appreciate your willingness to help me out, but I do this because I&rsquo;m concerned about society generally.</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong style="font-size: 12px;"><em>Here is what I think we should do.&nbsp; Why don&rsquo;t you put pressure on your relevant people to do their job and deal with pending requests? If they do their job, then my problem will also certainly be solved in the process. If they don&rsquo;t then my problem (like those of other numerous customers) will hang there up till God knows when.</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong style="font-size: 12px;"><em>May we then agree that we shall together publish the outcome next week? Have a great day.</em></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>That mail was sent and received by the relevant persons in the service organization. Guess what happened weeks after: NOTHING ! The problem remained unsolved. </strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong style="font-size: 12px;">The officials were quick to send public relations mails and apologise (which the customer appreciated) but that didn&rsquo;t change anything in the organization.</strong></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	(On January 16, 2014, TOM ASSOCIATES Training will present a unique seminar on the <strong>Generation Divide in Organizations Today.</strong> Book your Free Seat now.)</p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">Always check on our website: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><a href="http://www.tomassociatesng.com/" style="font-size: 12px;">www.tomassociatesng.com</a></p>\r\n<p style="margin-left:.25in;">\r\n	<span style="font-size: 12px;">Send mails: </span><a href="mailto:info@tomassociatesng.com" style="font-size: 12px;">info@tomassociatesng.com</a></p>\r\n', 'November 27, 2013'),
(10, 'YOUR SEVEN PARADOXICAL SUCCESSES', '<p align="left">\r\n	<strong>YOUR SEVEN PARADOXICAL SUCCESSES</strong></p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	<strong><span style="font-size: 12px;">For 2014, we in TOM ASSOCIATES want you to develop the ability to hold two ideas that look opposing in the mind at the same time, and yet retain the ability to succeed. Reason we are sending you these seven New Year success prayers:</span></strong></p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	<strong><span style="font-size: 12px;">1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; You will feel empowered even while respecting the hierarchy.</span></strong></p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	<strong>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; You will combine confidence and humility successfully.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	<strong>3.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; You will be able to envision success without underestimating competition.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	<strong>4.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Your focus on discipline will not prevent you from being creative.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	<strong>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; You will develop the capability to risk failure with your pursuit of success.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	<strong>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Your loyalty to your organization will not discourage you from criticizing it constructively.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	<strong>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; You will develop the ability of careful analyses without sacrificing quick action.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	<strong>These are our prayers for you for a Happy New Year.</strong></p>\r\n<p align="left">\r\n	<strong><span style="font-size: 12px;">TOM ASSOCIATES Annual Trainers Clinic for 2014 holds on Thursday January 16. It will explore the challenge of managing generational divide plaguing the workplace now, with special focus on the &quot;GENERATION Y&quot;. It will be great and it is FREE for you if you hold a position in HR, Training or L&amp;D in your organization. Programme Leader is Titi Akisanya, formerly of Phillips Consulting, Accenture, and Group HR Director for Coca-Cola International, Sub-Sahara Africa Group. Secure your seat now, by email.</span></strong></p>\r\n', 'January 5, 2014');
